However, as per an expert legal opinion obtained, the Company is not liable for such deposits. 4) Estimated amount of Contracts remaining to be executed on Capital Account in holding Company and not provided for (Net of Advances) Rs.12,58,138 (Previous Year Rs.19,23,440) 5 (a) The holding Company has given undertakings to the Financial Institutions that it will not, without their prior approval, transfer, assign, dispose off, pledge, charge or create any lien or in any way encumber its share holdings in Raigadh Papers Limited till the loans granted by the Financial Institutions to the said company remain outstanding. (b) The Company in past had approached the Hon'ble High Court of Mumbai against winding up of Raigadh Papers Limited to revive/recover old dues of Rs.135.68 lacs appearing as doubtful advances in Schedule 'J' hereof. During the year the Hon'ble High Court has passed the order in favour of the Company under the scheme of arrangement which is still pending with the official liquidator. 6) Land & Buildings and Plant & Machinery of the holding Company were revalued as on 30th June, 1980, 30th June, 1984, 30th June, 1986 (only Land and Buildings), 30th June, 1988 and 31st March, 1993. The total increase as a result of these revaluations were transferred to Revaluation Reserve in the respective years. All the above stated revaluations were carried out by an external approved valuer on the basis of market / replacement value of similar assets, using standard indices and after considering the obsolescence and age of individual assets. The revalued amounts, net of withdrawals, of Rs.67,89,29,516 for Land & Buildings and Rs.67,88,03,607 for Plant & Machinery (Previous Year Rs.67,89,29,516 and Rs.67,88,03,607, respectively) remain substituted for the historical costs in the gross block of Fixed Assets (Schedule 'E'). 71 Exceptional Items of holding Company include : 7) Exceptional Items of holding Company include :
